[30;1m401 | [0m[35m   //[0m
[30;1m402 | [0m[35m   // We do not allow cut points to be subnormal floats. Some environments still have issues dealing[0m
[30;1m403 | [0m[35m   // with them reproducibly, whereas setting them to zero should work in all environments and be re[0m
[30;1m404 | [0m[35m   // They might also not serialize/deserialize to JSON in all languages/environments.  Since we[0m
[30;1m405 | [0m[35m   // set subnormals to zero we cannot separate subnormals from each other, but having data that sho[0m
[30;1m406 | [0m[35m   // predict different outcomes in the subnormal range should be really rare, and any caller can re[0m
[30;1m407 | [0m[35m   // anyways by shifting the subnormals into the normal space themselves.[0m
